<subSubSection id="36E8E00D3749AF332889A6D5F87104E5" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="EA4BEC6ED281FB271D979D587EE047B9" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Diagnosis</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3BF54F1B611DC01C6A04808705534169" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
Body strongly depressed dorsoventrally and minutely granulate (Figs 
<figureCitation id="AC1E1AEDDF61CC902DC0EC158CD10D35" captionStart="Fig. 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Fig. 1. Amorphopus notabilis (female). A. Habitus in lateral view; B. Frons; C. Head, lateral lobes of pronotum and tegmina in lateral view; D. Habitus in dorsal view; E. Fore-femur; F. Mid-femur; G. Terminalia in ventral view; and H. In lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jor.29.33717.fig1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/395606" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">1A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="A39C13B21C3D9B2B66F27BEC87AFB315" captionStart="Fig. 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Fig. 2. Amorphopus notabilis (male). A. Habitus in lateral view; B. Frons; C. Head, lateral lobes of pronotum and tegmina in lateral view; D. Habitus in dorsal view; E. Fore-femur; F. Mid-femur; G. Terminalia in ventral view; and H. In lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jor.29.33717.fig2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/395607" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">2A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="3BF7D2401A07BB6BC47FAFE97C07DD1F" captionStart="Fig. 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Fig. 3. Live Amorphopus notabilis from Brazilian Amazon." figureDoi="10.3897/jor.29.33717.fig3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/395608" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">3</figureCitation>
). Eyes globose, not prominent; vertex anteriorly truncated; face very distinctly oblique; frontal costa with a wide scutellum between the lower part of the eyes, slightly compressed-elevated, sinuate below (Figs 
<figureCitation id="3093C666A2C1039B97D2B8B870D55452" captionStart="Fig. 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Fig. 1. Amorphopus notabilis (female). A. Habitus in lateral view; B. Frons; C. Head, lateral lobes of pronotum and tegmina in lateral view; D. Habitus in dorsal view; E. Fore-femur; F. Mid-femur; G. Terminalia in ventral view; and H. In lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jor.29.33717.fig1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/395606" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">1B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="9540840B14804383D320E5B2B038D7A9" captionStart="Fig. 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Fig. 2. Amorphopus notabilis (male). A. Habitus in lateral view; B. Frons; C. Head, lateral lobes of pronotum and tegmina in lateral view; D. Habitus in dorsal view; E. Fore-femur; F. Mid-femur; G. Terminalia in ventral view; and H. In lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jor.29.33717.fig2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/395607" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">2B</figureCitation>
). Lateral lobes of pronotum outwardly ampliate with both margins undulate. Tegmina oval and wings to the pronotum apex (Figs 
<figureCitation id="827D67FDB8AE005D99C8BEF55BD585C7" captionStart="Fig. 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Fig. 1. Amorphopus notabilis (female). A. Habitus in lateral view; B. Frons; C. Head, lateral lobes of pronotum and tegmina in lateral view; D. Habitus in dorsal view; E. Fore-femur; F. Mid-femur; G. Terminalia in ventral view; and H. In lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jor.29.33717.fig1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/395606" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">1C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="C446E842CF2D7BE8489952134A681EA4" captionStart="Fig. 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Fig. 2. Amorphopus notabilis (male). A. Habitus in lateral view; B. Frons; C. Head, lateral lobes of pronotum and tegmina in lateral view; D. Habitus in dorsal view; E. Fore-femur; F. Mid-femur; G. Terminalia in ventral view; and H. In lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jor.29.33717.fig2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/395607" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">2C</figureCitation>
). Legs short, fore and middle femora flattened, foliaceous and clypeate (Figs 
<figureCitation id="BC39D2F3D495E9C50415DB06A7F2D802" captionStart="Fig. 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Fig. 1. Amorphopus notabilis (female). A. Habitus in lateral view; B. Frons; C. Head, lateral lobes of pronotum and tegmina in lateral view; D. Habitus in dorsal view; E. Fore-femur; F. Mid-femur; G. Terminalia in ventral view; and H. In lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jor.29.33717.fig1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/395606" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">1E, F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="146855EA71183F60CAFFBE56DC285C96" captionStart="Fig. 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Fig. 2. Amorphopus notabilis (male). A. Habitus in lateral view; B. Frons; C. Head, lateral lobes of pronotum and tegmina in lateral view; D. Habitus in dorsal view; E. Fore-femur; F. Mid-femur; G. Terminalia in ventral view; and H. In lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jor.29.33717.fig2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/395607" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">2E, F</figureCitation>
), antegenicular tooth of the hind femur slightly developed, hind tibia very sparingly spinose, minutely serrulate; the first and third articles of the hind tarsi equal in length.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
